y be linked to the bioactive compound saponin.", "constituents": [], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Euphrasia tatarica var. brevipila are iridoid glycosides including euphorbicine, euphorbicine II, euphorbicine III and euphorbicine IV, flavonoids like rutin, quercetin, and kaempferol, phenolic acids including caffeic acid and ferulic acid, and phenylethanoid glycosides like verbascoside and leucoside A, which are responsible for its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties due to their ability to inhibit lipid peroxidation, scavenge free radicals, and modulate the immune system. The iridoid glycosides possess a wide range of pharmacological activities including anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and antiviral effects. The flavonoids and phenolic acids in Euphrasia tatarica var. brevipila exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities by scavenging free radicals and inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. The phenylethanoid glycosides have been shown to possess immunomodulatory and antioxidant activities. The combination of these bioactive compounds is responsible for the medicinal properties of Euphrasia tatarica var. brevipila.", "herb_names_common": [], "preparations": [{"name": "euphrasia tincture", "mentions": 17, "confidence_score": 159, "total_score": 2703}, {"name": "euphrasia infusion", "mentions": 17, "confidence_score": 133, "total_score": 2261}, {"name": "euphrasia salve", "mentions": 16, "confidence_score": 90, "total_score": 1440}, {"name": "eye drops", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 42, "total_score": 252}, {"name": "eyewash", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 33, "total_score": 132}, {"name": "ointment", "mentions": 6, "confidence_score": 32, "total_score": 192}, {"name": "euphrasia tea", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 30, "total_score": 150}, {"name": "euphrasia eye salve", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 26, "total_score": 104}, {"name": "euphrasia extract